Description: Feature selection methodology for classifying genetic sequences without alignment. 
Sequences are represented by adjacency matrices, enabling the identification of motifs (k-mers) that capture structural patterns relevant for distinguishing species by variants (subtypes). 
Evaluation uses machine learning models, including Random Forest and XGBoost.
